      "description": "This 2004 BMW M3 (E46) represents the pinnacle of analog performance, featuring the legendary S54B32 high-pressure 3.2L inline-six engine. The powertrain utilizes six individual throttle bodies and dual-VANOS variable valve timing to deliver a linear power band peaking at a visceral 8,000 RPM redline. Mated to a precise 6-speed Getrag manual transmission, the drivetrain is anchored by a factory variable M differential lock for superior lateral traction. This example is mechanically flawless, featuring documented subframe reinforcement and a comprehensive VANOS overhaul to ensure long-term structural and timing integrity. The chassis retains its original factory-spec rigidity, supported by a meticulously maintained suspension geometry that provides exceptional turn-in response and damping control. Finished in deep Carbon Black Metallic with an immaculate Nappa leather interior, this is a collector-grade specimen for the driver who demands mechanical perfection.",
